name: the monalisa
description:
The Mona Lisa (Italian: Monna Lisa [ˈmɔnna liːza] or La Gioconda [la dʒoˈkonda], French: La Joconde [la kɔ̃d]), is an oil painting on poplar wood created by Leonardo da Vinci in the 16th century. This painting is often regarded as one of the most famous paintings in the world and few other works of art have been the center of attention, study, mythology, and parody. This painting is owned by the French government and is on display at the Musée du Louvre in Paris.[2]

This half-body painting depicts a painting of a woman gazing at the visitor with an expression often described as enigmatic or mysterious.[3]
